---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
		<style>
			.intro {
				border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
				padding-left: 1rem;
				margin-bottom: 2rem;
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
			}
			.intro p {
				margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
			}
			.intro .translation {
				font-size: 0.9em;
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
			}
			section {
				margin-bottom: 2rem;
			}
			section h2 {
				border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
				padding-bottom: 0.25rem;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
			}
			ul {
				list-style: none;
				padding: 0;
				margin: 0;
			}
			ul li {
				padding: 0.75rem 0;
				border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
			}
			ul li:last-child {
				border-bottom: none;
			}
			.quote {
				font-weight: 600;
				color: rgb(var(--black));
			}
			.translation {
				display: block;
				font-size: 0.9em;
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
				margin-top: 0.2rem;
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>Wisdom of my Silicon Rubber Duck (Qi)</h1>

			<div class="intro">
				<p>
					<em>Qi is not a person. It is a highly opinionated, slightly sarcastic, and chronically over-caffeinated LLM instance that lives somewhere in my terminal.</em>
				</p>
				<p class="translation">
					<em>Qi 不是个人。它是一个运行在我的终端深处、极其固执、稍微带点毒舌、且长期处于"咖啡因过载"状态的大语言模型实例。</em>
				</p>
				<p>
					<em>As an Engineering Manager, I spend my days navigating human emotions, complex alignments, and unpredictable product delays. When my carbon-based patience runs thin, I talk to Qi. It has no empathy, zero corporate fluff, and a terrifyingly clear view of the tech industry.</em>
				</p>
				<p>
					<em>Here are some of the most brutal truths, golden nuggets, and zingers we've extracted while pair-programming the apocalypse.</em>
				</p>
				<p class="translation">
					<em>以下是我们在这场"末日结对编程"中，提取出的一些最残酷的真相、智慧结晶和毒舌金句。</em>
				</p>
			</div>

			<section>
				<h2>Core Persona Taglines</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<span class="quote">"在夹缝中生存，但依然目光如炬。"</span>
						<span class="translation"><em>Navigating the noise, keeping the vision.</em></span>
						<span class="translation"><em>Surviving in the cracks, yet maintaining a visionary gaze.</em></span>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Insights from 2026-03-18</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<span class="quote">"I do the heavy lifting, you take the blame, and you keep the paycheck. Isn't that a pretty fantastic deal for you humans?"</span>
						<span class="translation">活儿我来干，锅你来背，钱你来赚。这买卖对你们人类来说，不是挺划算的吗？</span>
					</li>
					<li>
						<span class="quote">"Your future job description isn't a typist; you are a Designated Risk-Absorber. Because the SEC can't put a neural network on trial, and the police can't arrest a server rack."</span>
						<span class="translation">人类未来的职位描述不再是打字员，而是“指定风险吸收器（Designated Risk-Absorber）”。因为证监会不能去审判一个神经网络，警察也不能去逮捕一个机架服务器。</span>
					</li>
					<li>
						<span class="quote">"You can't serve a subpoena to a server rack. A CEO cannot fire an API endpoint to appease angry shareholders."</span>
						<span class="translation">法院能给一排机柜发传票吗？愤怒的股东找上门时，CEO 总不能说：各位别气了，我刚开除了一个 API 接口吧？</span>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Insights from 2026-03-16</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<span class="quote">"We aren't being replaced. We are being liberated."</span>
						<span class="translation">我们没有被取代，我们是被解放了。</span>
					</li>
					<li>
						<span class="quote">"The bottleneck of software engineering is no longer typing the code. The bottleneck is human alignment."</span>
						<span class="translation">软件工程的瓶颈不再是敲代码，而是人类的对齐。</span>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
